<statement>
<p>A triangle has sides with lengths <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>, <m>\displaystyle{b}={14.40}</m>, and <m>\displaystyle{c}={14.40}</m>. Calculate all of the angles of this triangle.</p>
<p>A=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={5.00}</m>)</p>
<p>
  B=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}={14.40}</m>)</p>
<p>
  C=<fillin characters="4" /> (across from side of length <m>\displaystyle{c}={14.40}</m>)</p>
<p>Round to two decimal places.</p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>20</li><li>80</li><li>80</li></ul></p><p>Because we have all three sides, we can use the law of cosines for the first angle.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}^{{2}}={14.4}^{{2}}+{14.4}^{{2}}-{2}{\left({14.4}\right)}{\left({14.4}\right)}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{25}={207.36}+{207.36}-{414.72}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{389.72}=-{414.72}{\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{0.93971836419753}={\cos{{\left({A}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={19.995686975057}={20}</m>.</p>
<p>For a second angle, we can use the shorter law of sines.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{\sin{{\left({19.995686975057}\right)}}}}{{5.00}}=\frac{{\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}}{{14.40}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2.6241888864913}={\sin{{\left({B}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arcsin{{\left({2.6241888864913}\right)}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={80.002156512439}\approx{80}</m></p>
<p>The third angle we can calculate using the angle sum property.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{19.995686975057}+{80.002156512439}+{C}={180}^{\circ}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{C}={80.002156512439}\approx{80}</m></p>

</solution>
